@@ -0,0 +1,113 @@
+---
+date: "2026-06-11"
+status: done
+implements: [FR-E83]
+tags: [engine, cli, housekeeping, runs, journal]
+related_tasks:
+  - documents/tasks/2026/05/durable-run-lifecycle-replay.md
+---
+# Runs Prune Safe Cleanup
+
+## Goal
+
+Add a safe local run cleanup command that removes old terminal run
+directories while preserving active, locked, and unknown-state runs.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+Run folders accumulate under `<workflow-dir>/runs/`. Their only durable
+status source is `journal.jsonl`; cleanup must replay the journal instead of
+reading stale snapshots or inferring from folder names. Operators need a
+non-interactive CLI command for local filesystem cleanup only.
+
+### Current State
+
+`src/state/run-journal.ts` owns journal path construction and replay.
+`src/state/state.ts` owns `getRunDir()`. `src/state/lock.ts` owns
+`runs/.lock` path and JSON format. `src/cli.ts` routes `run`, `init`,
+`answer`, and `mcp`, but has no `runs prune` command.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- Reuse `getRunDir()`, `replayRunJournal()`, and lock helpers.
+- No new dependencies.
+- Treat missing or unreplayable journals as unknown state and keep them.
+- Never delete non-terminal or locked runs.
+- `--keep` must be a non-negative integer.
+- Non-interactive benchmark adaptation: selected variant is
+  architecturally-correct because it isolates prune selection in `src/state/`
+  and keeps `src/cli.ts` as thin argument routing.
+
+## Definition of Done
+
+- [x] FR-E83: selection keeps `N` newest terminal unlocked runs and deletes
+  only older terminal unlocked runs. Test:
+  `src/state/runs-prune_test.ts::runsPrunePlan keeps N newest terminal unlocked runs`.
+  Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: non-terminal, locked, missing-journal, and unreplayable-journal
+  runs are skipped with explicit reasons. Test:
+  `src/state/runs-prune_test.ts::runsPrunePlan skips protected and unknown runs`.
+  Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: `--keep 0` deletes all terminal unlocked runs and `--dry-run`
+  deletes nothing. Test:
+  `src/state/runs-prune_test.ts::pruneRuns applies keep zero and dry run`.
+  Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: bad `--keep` is rejected with clear non-zero CLI error. Test:
+  `src/cli_test.ts::FR-E83 parseRunsPruneArgs rejects bad keep values`.
+  Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: CLI help lists `runs prune`. Test:
+  `src/cli_test.ts::FR-E83 usage includes runs prune`.
+  Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: SRS section added to
+  `documents/requirements-engine/06-distribution-and-housekeeping.md` with
+  acceptance criteria and task back-pointer. Test:
+  `manual — Codex`. Evidence:
+  `rg 'FR-E83|runs prune' documents/requirements-engine.md documents/requirements-engine/06-distribution-and-housekeeping.md documents/index.md`.
+
+## Solution
+
+1. Add `src/state/runs-prune.ts`.
+   - Define `RunPrunePlan`, `RunPruneEntry`, and skip reason types.
+   - Enumerate direct child directories of `<workflowDir>/runs`.
+   - Ignore non-run entries such as `.lock`.
+   - For each directory, use `getRunDir(runId, workflowDir)` to resolve the
+     run path, `replayRunJournal(runDir)` to recover `status` and
+     `started_at`, and `defaultLockPath()` + `readLockInfo()` to protect the
+     locked run.
+   - Sort deletable terminal runs by `started_at` descending with `run_id` as a
+     deterministic tie-breaker, keep the newest `N`, delete the remaining
+     oldest.
+   - Return a plan containing deleted, kept, skipped, and dry-run status.
+   - Error handling: replay/read errors become skipped unknown-state entries;
+     filesystem delete errors throw clearly.
+2. Add `src/state/runs-prune_test.ts`.
+   - Build temp workflow fixtures with engine-shaped journals via
+     `RunJournalWriter`.
+   - Cover newest retention, protected skips, unknown journals, `--keep 0`,
+     dry-run, and actual deletion.
+3. Extend `src/cli.ts`.
+   - Add `parseRunsPruneArgs(args)` using the existing manual parser style.
+   - Add `runRunsPrune(args)` for `flowai-workflow runs prune --workflow <dir>
+     --keep <N> [--dry-run]`.
+   - Route `runs prune` before the default unknown-subcommand branch; do not
+     pass it through `run` or generic flag parsing.
+   - Print deleted, kept, and skipped counts plus per-run skip reasons.
+   - Use the same summary shape for dry-run and delete modes, with labels
+     distinguishing `would delete` from `deleted`.
+   - Add `runs prune` to usage output.
+4. Extend `src/cli_test.ts`.
+   - Unit-test prune argument parsing, bad `--keep`, and help text helper.
+5. Update docs.
+   - Add FR-E83 to `documents/requirements-engine.md`,
+     `documents/requirements-engine/06-distribution-and-housekeeping.md`,
+     and `documents/index.md`.
+   - Add SDS notes for `runs-prune.ts` and CLI routing.
+6. Verification.
+   - Run focused RED checks before implementation.
+   - Run `deno task check` after GREEN and after final documentation sync.
+
+## Follow-ups
+
+- Future listing or inspection command stays out of scope.
